garage door openers troubleshooting";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/96/29/06/9629066dac2a034974050d1366ad1375.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ9CLYV6xRpZG0vPW2WAGSuhVVRLONUTtszPQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:627;s:6:"height";i:736;s:6:"source";s:48:"https://za.pinterest.com/pin/401664860490638819/";s:6:"domain";s:16:"za.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:64:{i:0;s:83:"To be more specific your garage door may not close properly while its cold outside.";i:1;s:132:"Your garage door not closing properly could be due to frozen grease condensation on the sensors or problems with certain components.";i:2;s:78:"The panels of your garage door could also freeze due to the cold temperatures.";i:3;s:46:"Cold Weather Garage Door Safety Sensor Issues.";i:4;s:59:"Cold weather can affect safety sensors in a number of ways.";i:5;s:126:"When there is an issue with your safety sensors the opener will interpret this as an obstruction and refuse to close the door.";i:6;s:151:"If the issue is with the sensors youll likely find that you can use the garage door remote or wall-mounted switch to open the door but not to close it.";i:7;s:29:"Garage doors can be spiteful.";i:8;s:74:"Cold weather can particularly affect your garage door since it is outside.";i:9;s:163:"In cold weather conditions your garage door opener may strain to open the door which could create greater energy costs to you or cause the door or opener to break.";i:10;s:44:"Reasons why your garage door is not closing.";i:11;s:84:"Check for your garage door sensors Your garage door sensors are positioned just six.";i:12;s:98:"A common cause of a garage door that wont close or open during cold weather is a frozen threshold.";i:13;s:75:"This event happens when the ground is wet usually from rain and it freezes.";i:14;s:131:"If you believe that your garage door is stuck due to being frozen its important not to try opening it until youve cleared the area.";i:15;s:156:"Here are a few common garage door issues homeowners encounter in cold weather along with the steps to safely resolve the issue and protect your garage door.";i:16;s:30:"Check Your Garage Door Opener.";i:17;s:145:"If your garage door is not working properly and you have an automatic garage door opener disconnect the opener and try to open the door manually.";i:18;s:58:"If the door opens fine the issue could be related to your.";i:19;s:30:"Ive got the same problem here.";i:20;s:88:"When it gets cold I need to hold the button on the wall to get the garage door to close.";i:21;s:47:"Remotes dont work for closing only for opening.";i:22;s:115:"Ive checked the door manually and it moves up and down fine and the sensor is clear and appears to be working fine.";i:23;s:41:"My unit is a Stanley chain driven opener.";i:24;s:83:"Make sure they are aligned and that the lenss are wiped clean from debris and dirt.";i:25;s:71:"Be sure not to block the sensors with snow snow shovels or other items.";i:26;s:86:"If the sensors are blocked or out of alignment the garage door will not shut properly.";i:27;s:50:"Very cold temperatures can cause springs to break.";i:28;s:74:"Disconnect the garage door from the opener and manually open and close it.";i:29;s:98:"If it opens and closes without great difficulty this rules out track and garage door panel issues.";i:30;s:37:"Garage doors operate in cold weather.";i:31;s:58:"Its -30F where I live and everyone here has a garage door.";i:32;s:77:"You can buy a garage door opener service kit from Home Depot for a few bucks.";i:33;s:113:"Its basically a can of silicon lubricant to spray on the hinges and a tube of grease to put on the central track.";i:34;s:145:"You should also increase the torque by turning the dial on the opener motor - on mine there are separate settings for opening and closing torque.";i:35;s:62:"I have a sears garage door opener on 2 different garage doors.";i:36;s:135:"When the weather gets very cold in the low 30s and below the opener will not function in the down direction works fine in the up direc.";i:37;s:75:"Good Morning My Lift Master Model 1245K has been acting up in cold weather.";i:38;s:211:"If youre still having problems then the cold temperatures may have caused the brackets that hold the runners for the garage door in place to become misaligned due to contraction of the metal in the cold weather.";i:39;s:57:"Check them to make sure theyre correctly in place and if.";i:40;s:207:"Well every winter typically when its 10 below the garage door decides that it doesnt want to work and this is the outside panel on the garage door and the remote openers decide that theyre not going to work.";i:41;s:43:"I guess they want us to get out and freeze.";i:42;s:73:"Leslie chuckles One more piece of the equation is when we do get out and.";i:43;s:43:"Common Cold Weather Garage Door Problems 1.";i:44;s:34:"Malfunctioning Garage Door Opener.";i:45;s:123:"The opener is that small electrically powered box-like device at the top of the door that controls its opening and closing.";i:46;s:104:"Cold temperatures can hinder the performance of the openers motor and other essential system components.";i:47;s:60:"What to Do If the Garage Door Stops Working Due to the Cold.";i:48;s:157:"If its uncomfortably cold outside and your garage door has suddenly stopped working your first step should always be to replace the batteries in your remote.";i:49;s:28:"The batteries should all be.";i:50;s:73:"In NapervilleIL the Garage Door Wont Close cold weather issues - YouTube.";i:51;s:43:"The remotes will not close the garage door.";i:52;s:22:"They can only open it.";i:53;s:79:"You may find that the door will only move an inch or so in the close direction.";i:54;s:114:"When this happens your garage door will only close by holding down on the wall button until the door fully closes.";i:55;s:78:"This method is the only way to override the safety sensors and close the door.";i:56;s:91:"I have a Crafstman 12 HP garage door opener in my garage that is a little over 5 years old.";i:57;s:201:"The problem I have been having during the past couple winters is that when the temperature gets frigid cold usually anything below 30 degrees F my garage door only opens about 10 inches and then stops.";i:58;s:82:"I usually have to open and close the garage door 5-10 times before the door opens.";i:59;s:33:"Discussion Starter 1 Feb 21 2019.";i:60;s:91:"Hello My 2004 craftsman garage door opener gets stuck on the down movement around the bend.";i:61;s:46:"This happens during extreme cold weather only.";i:62;s:27:"Works well in warm weather.";i:63;s:129:"Should i keep increasing the down force screwdriver turn until it works in cold weather or is it something else like the railing.";}}